subSubSection.paragraph:
Prostheceraeus vittatus
is known from the North Atlantic coasts of the United Kingdom, France, Ireland, Scandinavia, Norway, Denmark, from the Mediterranean shores in Italy (Gulf of Naples) (
Faubel and Warwick 2005
) and Spain (Catalonia) (
Novell 2003
). This is the first record for the species from the North Atlantic side of the Iberian Peninsula.
